comments.body:
> For me, the issue was my SSH agent with a lot of keys already.

Same here, i just ran into this issue. I just temporarily unset SSH_AUTH_SOCK. 

@samuel-phan didn't know about `ssh-add -D`, thx!

@smakinen when you observe this failure, can you also verify if gvproxy is running or not?  I've picked up this issue and I am currently honing in on a fix.  Like @ashley-cui , I very much struggle to replicate this issue so I have had to depend on others to get answers and give me access to their machine.

Right now, I believe that all of these reports are really the combination of more than one bug ... one of which seems to always be this timing issue.

For the timing issue, I have been experimenting with altering the "ready" service in the machine to trigger later (like after NM).  I may also make it trigger even later, like sometime around when zincati fires which is a pretty good indicator we are actually up and running.
